# Aim Brain Engine Roadmap

## Product direction

Aim Brain is a local-first aim-training coach. The engine is the actual product core. UI polish matters, but it comes after trustworthy data and useful decisions.

## Phase 1 — Engine foundation

Goal: make raw run data produce reliable scenario stats.

Build:

- ScoreRun type
- Scenario type
- RankThreshold type
- accepted-run filtering
- PB/latest/all-average/last-10
- basic consistency
- sample data
- test cases

Exit condition:

- The app can take raw runs and return scenario summaries without using UI calculations.

## Phase 2 — Scenario and category logic

Goal: prevent data chaos.

Build:

- scenario database shape
- scenario aliases
- scenario name normalization
- platform-aware matching
- category/subcategory mapping
- unresolved scenario output

Exit condition:

- Imported names can be mapped or safely flagged for review.

## Phase 3 — Rank conversion

Goal: support Voltaic-style progress without lying.

Build:

- rank scale
- threshold set model
- score-to-rank conversion
- progress to next rank
- `progress_only` fallback

Exit condition:

- Scenarios with thresholds show rank progress; scenarios without thresholds honestly say no threshold data.

## Phase 4 — Diagnosis

Goal: make the app explain what matters.

Build:

- weakest category
- strongest category
- neglected category
- inconsistent category
- plateau detection
- Master readiness
- category imbalance

Exit condition:

- The app can say what is blocking the user and why.

## Phase 5 — Recommendation

Goal: turn analysis into today’s action.

Build:

- session type selection
- recommended categories
- recommended scenarios
- avoid-overtraining categories
- success condition
- coach summary

Exit condition:

- The app can tell the user what to train today and what result would prove it worked.

## Phase 6 — Product integration

Goal: the UI becomes a display layer for the engine.

Build:

- Home cards from engine output
- Summary from engine output
- Coach Report from engine output
- Weekly Coach from engine output
- evidence-based explanation cards

Exit condition:

- No important coaching logic lives inside React components.
